additionalTextInformation.text:
The painter of this retable was trained in Cranach‘s workshop and sourced inspiration from his collection of templates and preparatory material. He also drew on Dürer prints as a basis for his compositions. Results of a technical examination of the painting do not indicate that it was executed in the Wittenberg workshop. As Friedrich III is represented on this painting future research should concentrate on finding out more about this particular commission and attempt to establish the relationship of the artist responsible for the Mittenwald Retable (http://lucascranach.org/DE_MKM_NONE-MKM001C) with the elector of Saxony.

[see Heydenreich 2016, 149-150]

pageContext.description:
Recto: The Virgin sits with the infant Christ at the left edge of the composition and receives a gift from the eldest king, who kneels before her. Behind him are the second king and Friedrich III of Saxony in the role of the third wise man. 
Verso: A full-length representation of St Augustine, wearing bishop's vestments and standing on a thin strip of ground against a black background. The saint is turned to the left and holds a book in his hands on which his attribute of the pierced heart is placed, as well as a crosier. 
[Görres, cda 2017]

tests.text:
Lime wood
[Examination report, Peter Klein, 04. Sept. 2007]

The Adoration of the Shepherds [right wing, recto]
DESCRIPTION

Tools/Material: 
- fluid, black medium, brush 

Type/Ductus: 
- freehand underdrawing
- thin to somewhat broader lines; possibly some washes 

Function: 
- relatively binding for the final painted version; lines of varying widths delineate the main contours, describe essential details and facial features; no representation of volume with hatching-strokes 

Deviations: 
- very few corrections were made to forms during the painting process. 

INTERPRETATION

Attribution: 
- painter of the Mittenwald Retable


St Augustine [right wing, verso]
DESCRIPTION

Tools/Material: 
- fluid, black medium, brush 

Type/Ductus: 
- freehand underdrawing
- thin to somewhat broader lines; possibly some washes 

Function: 
- relatively binding for the final painted version; lines of varying strengths delineate the main contours, describe essential details and facial features; no representation of volumes with hatching-strokes 

Deviations: 
- a few corrections were made to forms during the painting process, small changes 

INTERPRETATION

Attribution: 
- painter of the Mittenwald Retable
[Sandner, Smith-Contini, Heydenreich, cda 2017]
